  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marketing Executive (Singapore)",
  "description": "<p>As part of a bold rebranding initiative, <strong>Glamour+</strong>, <strong>Glow Haven Aesthetics &amp; Wellness</strong>, and <strong>Salon V Hair Studio</strong> have emerged from the award-winning legacy of Avone Beauty Secrets — each brand now specializing in its own area of expertise to better serve our clients.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Together, we represent one of Singapore’s most dynamic and fast-growing groups in the beauty and wellness industry, with a renewed focus on innovation, personalization, and excellence in service.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are looking for <strong>motivated Marketing Executive </strong>to help carry out our marketing plans and bring our campaigns to life. If you’re creative, detail-oriented, and excited about content creation for the purpose of lead generation and building brand awareness in the beauty and wellness space, we’d love to meet you.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Execute marketing campaigns and promotions across digital, social media, print, retail, and events</p>\n<p>· Generate engaging content for social media platforms, websites, and other digital channels</p>\n<p>· Support day-to-day management of the marketing calendar, ensuring timely posting and campaign rollouts</p>\n<p>· Assist with market research, competitor tracking, and reporting on campaign performance</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with designers, vendors, and internal teams to deliver quality, on-brand materials</p>\n<p>· Support influencer collaborations, partnerships, and PR initiatives</p>\n<p>· Ensure brand consistency across all communications and content</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· 1–2 years of marketing or content creation experience (beauty, retail, or lifestyle industries preferred)</p>\n<p>· Strong knowledge of social media platforms and content marketing</p>\n<p>· Hands-on skills with Canva, Adobe Photoshop/Illustrator, or similar tools</p>\n<p>· Good communication and copywriting skills in both English and Chinese (written and spoken)</p>\n<p>· Must be Singaporean or PR (due to quota limitations)</p>\n<p>· Creative, proactive, and able to work independently as well as with a team</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>This role is ideal for someone ready to make a real impact — to shape brands, influence growth, and lead with both creativity and data. Join us in reimagining the future of beauty and wellness.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Basic up to $3500 before performance incentives</p>\n<p>· Flexible work hours</p>\n<p>· Staff discounts and privileges from Company-owned service establishments</p>\n<p>· Office located at near Tai Seng MRT (Circle Line)</p>\n<p>· Clean, quiet and comfortable working environment</p>",
